02303         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02304             if ((offset <= 1))
02305                 return 0x000001000020006Cull + ((offset) & 1) * 0x100000000ull;
02306             break;
02307         case OCTEON_CN66XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02308             if ((offset == 0) || ((offset >= 2) && (offset <= 3)))
02309                 return 0x000000000020006Cull;
02310             break;
02311         case OCTEON_CN63XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02312             if ((offset <= 1))
02313                 return 0x000000000020006Cull + ((offset) & 1) * 0x100000000ull;
02314             break;
02315     }
02316     cvmx_warn("CVMX_SRIOMAINTX_TX_DROP (offset = %lu) not supported on this chip\n", offset);
02317     return 0x000001000020006Cull + ((offset) & 1) * 0x100000000ull;
02318 }
02319 #else
02320 static inline uint64_t CVMX_SRIOMAINTX_TX_DROP(unsigned long offset)
02321 {
02322     switch(cvmx_get_octeon_family()) {
02323         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02324             return 0x000001000020006Cull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
02325         case OCTEON_CN66XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02326             return 0x000000000020006Cull;
02327         case OCTEON_CN63XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
02328             return 0x000000000020006Cull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
02329     }
02330     return 0x000001000020006Cull + (offset) * 0x100000000ull;
02331 }
02332 #endif
02333

02382 /**
02383  * cvmx_sriomaint#_bar1_idx#
02384  *
02385  * Contains address index and control bits for access to memory ranges of BAR1.
02386  * This register specifies the OCTEON address, endian swap and cache status associated with each
02387  * of the 16 BAR1 entries.  The local address bits used are based on the BARSIZE field located in
02388  * SRIOMAINT()_M2S_BAR1_START0.  This register is only writeable over SRIO if
02389  * SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_BAR1] is zero.
02390  */
02391 union cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx {
02392     uint32_t u32;
02393     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx_s {
02394 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02395     uint32_t reserved_6_31                : 26;
02396     uint32_t es                           : 2;  /**< Endian swap mode.
02397                                                          0x0 = No swap.
02398                                                          0x1 = 64-bit swap bytes [ABCD_EFGH] -> [HGFE_DCBA].
02399                                                          0x2 = 32-bit swap words [ABCD_EFGH] -> [DCBA_HGFE].
02400                                                          0x3 = 32-bit word exch  [ABCD_EFGH] -> [EFGH_ABCD]. */
02401     uint32_t nca                          : 1;  /**< Non-cacheable access mode.  When set, transfers
02402                                                          through this window are not cacheable. */
02403     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;
02404     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< When set the selected index address is valid. */
02405 #else
02406     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
02407     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;
02408     uint32_t nca                          : 1;
02409     uint32_t es                           : 2;
02410     uint32_t reserved_6_31                : 26;
02411 #endif
02412     } s;
02413     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx_cn63xx {
02414 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02415     uint32_t reserved_30_31               : 2;
02416     uint32_t la                           : 22; /**< L2/DRAM Address bits [37:16]
02417                                                          Not all LA[21:0] bits are used by SRIO hardware,
02418                                                          depending on SRIOMAINT(0..1)_M2S_BAR1_START1[BARSIZE].
02419 
02420                                                                                  Become
02421                                                                                  L2/DRAM
02422                                                                                  Address  Entry
02423                                                          BARSIZE   LA Bits Used   Bits    Size
02424                                                             0        LA[21:0]    [37:16]   64KB
02425                                                             1        LA[21:1]    [37:17]  128KB
02426                                                             2        LA[21:2]    [37:18]  256KB
02427                                                             3        LA[21:3]    [37:19]  512KB
02428                                                             4        LA[21:4]    [37:20]    1MB
02429                                                             5        LA[21:5]    [37:21]    2MB
02430                                                             6        LA[21:6]    [37:22]    4MB
02431                                                             7        LA[21:7]    [37:23]    8MB
02432                                                             8        LA[21:8]    [37:24]   16MB
02433                                                             9        LA[21:9]    [37:25]   32MB
02434                                                            10        LA[21:10]   [37:26]   64MB
02435                                                            11        LA[21:11]   [37:27]  128MB
02436                                                            12        LA[21:12]   [37:28]  256MB
02437                                                            13        LA[21:13]   [37:29]  512MB */
02438     uint32_t reserved_6_7                 : 2;
02439     uint32_t es                           : 2;  /**< Endian Swap Mode.
02440                                                          0 = No Swap
02441                                                          1 = 64-bit Swap Bytes [ABCD_EFGH] -> [HGFE_DCBA]
02442                                                          2 = 32-bit Swap Words [ABCD_EFGH] -> [DCBA_HGFE]
02443                                                          3 = 32-bit Word Exch  [ABCD_EFGH] -> [EFGH_ABCD] */
02444     uint32_t nca                          : 1;  /**< Non-Cacheable Access Mode.  When set, transfers
02445                                                          through this window are not cacheable. */
02446     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;
02447     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< When set the selected index address is valid. */
02448 #else
02449     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
02450     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;
02451     uint32_t nca                          : 1;
02452     uint32_t es                           : 2;
02453     uint32_t reserved_6_7                 : 2;
02454     uint32_t la                           : 22;
02455     uint32_t reserved_30_31               : 2;
02456 #endif
02457     } cn63xx;
02458     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx_cn63xx cn63xxp1;
02459     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx_cn63xx cn66xx;
02460     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_bar1_idxx_cnf75xx {
02461 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02462     uint32_t la                           : 26; /**< L2/DRAM Address bits [41:16].
02463                                                          Not all LA[25:0] bits are used by SRIO hardware,
02464                                                          depending on SRIOMAINT()_M2S_BAR1_START1[BARSIZE].
02465                                                          <pre>
02466                                                          Become
02467                                                          L2/DRAM
02468                                                          Address  Entry
02469                                                          BARSIZE  LA Bits Used   Bits     Size
02470                                                          0        LA[25:0]    [41:16]     64KB
02471                                                          1        LA[25:1]    [41:17]    128KB
02472                                                          2        LA[25:2]    [41:18]    256KB
02473                                                          3        LA[25:3]    [41:19]    512KB
02474                                                          4        LA[25:4]    [41:20]      1MB
02475                                                          5        LA[25:5]    [41:21]      2MB
02476                                                          6        LA[25:6]    [41:22]      4MB
02477                                                          7        LA[25:7]    [41:23]      8MB
02478                                                          8        LA[25:8]    [41:24]     16MB
02479                                                          9        LA[25:9]    [41:25]     32MB
02480                                                          10       LA[25:10]   [41:26]     64MB
02481                                                          11       LA[25:11]   [41:27]    128MB
02482                                                          12       LA[25:12]   [41:28]    256MB
02483                                                          13       LA[25:13]   [41:29]    512MB
02484                                                          </pre> */
02485     uint32_t es                           : 2;  /**< Endian swap mode.
02486                                                          0x0 = No swap.
02487                                                          0x1 = 64-bit swap bytes [ABCD_EFGH] -> [HGFE_DCBA].
02488                                                          0x2 = 32-bit swap words [ABCD_EFGH] -> [DCBA_HGFE].
02489                                                          0x3 = 32-bit word exch  [ABCD_EFGH] -> [EFGH_ABCD]. */
02490     uint32_t nca                          : 1;  /**< Non-cacheable access mode.  When set, transfers
02491                                                          through this window are not cacheable. */
02492     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;
02493     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< When set the selected index address is valid. */
02494 #else

02496     uint32_t reserved_1_2                 : 2;

02500 #endif

02551 /**
02552  * cvmx_sriomaint#_core_enables
02553  *
02554  * This register displays the reset state of the OCTEON core logic while the SRIO link is
02555  * running.
02556  * The bit should be set after the software has initialized the chip to allow memory operations.
02557  */
02558 union cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables {
02559     uint32_t u32;
02560     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables_s {
02561 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02562     uint32_t reserved_5_31                : 27;
02563     uint32_t halt                         : 1;  /**< CNXXXX currently in reset.
02564                                                          0 = All CNXXXX resources are available.
02565                                                          1 = The CNXXXX is in reset. When this bit is set,
02566                                                          SRIO maintenance registers can be accessed,
02567                                                          but BAR0, BAR1, and BAR2 cannot be. */
02568     uint32_t imsg1                        : 1;  /**< Allow incoming message unit 1 operations.
02569                                                          Note: This bit is cleared when the CNXXXX is reset.
02570                                                          0 = SRIO incoming messages to unit 1 ignored and
02571                                                          return error response.
02572                                                          1 = SRIO incoming messages to unit 1 allowed. */
02573     uint32_t imsg0                        : 1;  /**< Allow incoming message unit 0 operations
02574                                                          Note: This bit is cleared when the CNXXX is reset.
02575                                                          0 = SRIO incoming messages to unit 0 ignored and
02576                                                          return error response.
02577                                                          1 = SRIO incoming messages to unit 0 allowed. */
02578     uint32_t doorbell                     : 1;  /**< Allow inbound doorbell operations
02579                                                          Note: This bit is cleared when the CNXXXX is reset.
02580                                                          0 = SRIO doorbell OPs ignored and return error
02581                                                          response.
02582                                                          1 = SRIO doorbell OPs allowed. */
02583     uint32_t memory                       : 1;  /**< Allow inbound/outbound memory operations.
02584                                                          Note: This bit is cleared when the CNXXXX is reset.
02585                                                          0 = SRIO incoming nwrites and swrites are
02586                                                          dropped.  Incoming nreads, atomics and
02587                                                          nwriters return responses with ERROR status.
02588                                                          SRIO incoming maintenance BAR memory accesses
02589                                                          are processed normally.
02590                                                          Outgoing store operations are dropped.
02591                                                          Outgoing load operations are not issued and
02592                                                          return all 1's with an ERROR status.
02593                                                          In flight operations started while the bit is
02594                                                          set in both directions will complete normally.
02595                                                          1 = SRIO memory read/write OPs allowed */
02596 #else
02597     uint32_t memory                       : 1;
02598     uint32_t doorbell                     : 1;
02599     uint32_t imsg0                        : 1;
02600     uint32_t imsg1                        : 1;
02601     uint32_t halt                         : 1;
02602     uint32_t reserved_5_31                : 27;
02603 #endif
02604     } s;
02605     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables_s cn63xx;
02606     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables_s cn63xxp1;
02607     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables_s cn66xx;
02608     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_core_enables_s cnf75xx;

02715     uint32_t atom_swp                     : 1;  /**< PE does not support atomic swap.
02716                                                          This is a RO copy of SRIO()_IP_FEATURE[OPS]<3>. */

02718                                                          This is a RO copy of SRIO()_IP_FEATURE[OPS]<2>. */

02738     uint32_t tlb_inv                      : 1;

02756 /**
02757  * cvmx_sriomaint#_erb_attr_capt
02758  *
02759  * This register contains the information captured during the error.
02760  * The hardware will not update this register (i.e. this register is locked) while
02761  * VALID is set in this CSR.
02762  * The hardware sets SRIO_INT_REG[PHY_ERB] every time it sets VALID in this CSR.
02763  * To handle the interrupt, the following procedure may be best:
02764  *
02765  * (1) read this CSR, corresponding SRIOMAINT()_ERB_ERR_DET, SRIOMAINT()_ERB_PACK_SYM_CAPT,
02766  * SRIOMAINT()_ERB_PACK_CAPT_1, SRIOMAINT()_ERB_PACK_CAPT_2, and SRIOMAINT()_ERB_PACK_CAPT_3.
02767  * (2) Write VALID in this CSR to 0.
02768  * (3) clear SRIO_INT_REG[PHY_ERB].
02769  */
02770 union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt {
02771     uint32_t u32;
02772     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt_s {
02773 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02774     uint32_t inf_type                     : 3;  /**< Type of information logged.
02775                                                          0x0 = Packet.
02776                                                          0x2 = Short control symbol
02777                                                          (use only first capture register).
02778                                                          0x4 = Implementation specific error reporting.
02779                                                          else = Reserved */
02780     uint32_t err_type                     : 5;  /**< The encoded value of the 31 minus the bit in
02781                                                          SRIOMAINT()_ERB_ERR_DET that describes the error
02782                                                          captured in SRIOMAINT()_ERB_()CAPT Registers.
02783                                                          (For example a value of 5 indicates 31-5 = bit 26). */
02784     uint32_t err_info                     : 20; /**< Error info.
02785                                                          <pre>
02786                                                          ERR_TYPE Bits   Description
02787                                                          -------- ------ -----------
02788                                                          0        23     TX Protocol Error
02789                                                                   22     RX Protocol Error
02790                                                                   21     TX Link Response Timeout
02791                                                                   20     TX ACKID Timeout
02792                                                                   - 19:16  Reserved
02793                                                                   - 15:12  TX Protocol ID
02794                                                                            1 = Rcvd Unexpected Link Response
02795                                                                            2 = Rcvd Link Response before Req
02796                                                                            3 = Rcvd NACK servicing NACK
02797                                                                            4 = Rcvd NACK
02798                                                                            5 = Rcvd RETRY servicing RETRY
02799                                                                            6 = Rcvd RETRY servicing NACK
02800                                                                            7 = Rcvd ACK servicing RETRY
02801                                                                            8 = Rcvd ACK servicing NACK
02802                                                                            9 = Unexp ACKID on ACK or RETRY
02803                                                                            10 = Unexp ACK or RETRY
02804                                                                  - 11:8   Reserved
02805                                                                 - 7:4   RX Protocol ID
02806                                                                            1 = Rcvd EOP w/o Prev SOP
02807                                                                            2 = Rcvd STOMP w/o Prev SOP
02808                                                                            3 = Unexp RESTART
02809                                                                            4 = Redundant Status from LinkReq
02810                                                          9-16   23:20  RX K Bits
02811                                                                 - 19:0   Reserved
02812                                                          26     23:20  RX K Bits
02813                                                                 - 19:0   Reserved
02814                                                          27     23:12  Type
02815                                                                         0x000 TX
02816                                                                         0x010 RX
02817                                                                 - 11:8   RX or TX Protocol ID (see above)
02818                                                                 - 7:4   Reserved
02819                                                          30     23:20  RX K Bits
02820                                                                 - 19:0   Reserved
02821                                                          31     23:16  ACKID Timeout 0x2
02822                                                                 - 15:14  Reserved
02823                                                                 - 13:8   AckID
02824                                                                 - 7:4   Reserved
02825                                                          </pre>
02826                                                          All others ERR_TYPEs are reserved. */
02827     uint32_t reserved_1_3                 : 3;
02828     uint32_t valid                        : 1;  /**< This bit is set by hardware to indicate that the
02829                                                          packet/control symbol capture registers contain
02830                                                          valid information. For control symbols, only
02831                                                          capture register 0 will contain meaningful
02832                                                          information.  This bit must be cleared by software
02833                                                          to allow capture of other errors. */
02834 #else
02835     uint32_t valid                        : 1;
02836     uint32_t reserved_1_3                 : 3;
02837     uint32_t err_info                     : 20;
02838     uint32_t err_type                     : 5;
02839     uint32_t inf_type                     : 3;
02840 #endif
02841     } s;
02842     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt_s cn63xx;
02843     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt_cn63xxp1 {
02844 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02845     uint32_t inf_type                     : 3;  /**< Type of Information Logged.
02846                                                          000 - Packet
02847                                                          010 - Short Control Symbol
02848                                                                (use only first capture register)
02849                                                          All Others Reserved */
02850     uint32_t err_type                     : 5;  /**< The encoded value of the 31 minus the bit in
02851                                                          SRIOMAINT(0..1)_ERB_ERR_DET that describes the error
02852                                                          captured in SRIOMAINT(0..1)_ERB_*CAPT Registers.
02853                                                          (For example a value of 5 indicates 31-5 = bit 26) */
02854     uint32_t reserved_1_23                : 23;
02855     uint32_t valid                        : 1;  /**< This bit is set by hardware to indicate that the
02856                                                          Packet/control symbol capture registers contain
02857                                                          valid information. For control symbols, only
02858                                                          capture register 0 will contain meaningful
02859                                                          information.  This bit must be cleared by software
02860                                                          to allow capture of other errors. */
02861 #else
02862     uint32_t valid                        : 1;
02863     uint32_t reserved_1_23                : 23;
02864     uint32_t err_type                     : 5;
02865     uint32_t inf_type                     : 3;
02866 #endif
02867     } cn63xxp1;
02868     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt_s cn66xx;
02869     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_attr_capt_s cnf75xx;

03001 /**
03002  * cvmx_sriomaint#_erb_err_rate
03003  *
03004  * This register is used with the error rate threshold register to monitor and control
03005  * the reporting of transmission errors.
03006  */
03007 union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate {
03008     uint32_t u32;
03009     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_s {
03010 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03011     uint32_t err_bias                     : 8;  /**< These bits provide the error rate bias value.
03012                                                          0x00 = do not decrement the error rate counter.
03013                                                          0x01 = decrement every 1ms (+/-34%).
03014                                                          0x02 = decrement every 10ms (+/-34%).
03015                                                          0x04 = decrement every 100ms (+/-34%).
03016                                                          0x08 = decrement every 1s (+/-34%).
03017                                                          0x10 = decrement every 10s (+/-34%).
03018                                                          0x20 = decrement every 100s (+/-34%).
03019                                                          0x40 = decrement every 1000s (+/-34%).
03020                                                          0x80 = decrement every 10000s (+/-34%).
03021                                                          _ All other values are reserved */
03022     uint32_t reserved_18_23               : 6;
03023     uint32_t rate_lim                     : 2;  /**< These bits limit the incrementing of the error
03024                                                          rate counter above the failed threshold trigger.
03025                                                          0x0 = only count 2 errors above.
03026                                                          0x1 = only count 4 errors above.
03027                                                          0x2 = only count 16 error above.
03028                                                          0x3 = do not limit incrementing the error rate count. */
03029     uint32_t pk_rate                      : 8;  /**< Peak value attainted by the error rate counter */
03030     uint32_t rate_cnt                     : 8;  /**< These bits maintain a count of the number of transmission errors that have been
03031                                                          detected by the port, decremented by the error rate bias mechanism, to create an
03032                                                          indication of the link error rate. */
03033 #else
03034     uint32_t rate_cnt                     : 8;
03035     uint32_t pk_rate                      : 8;
03036     uint32_t rate_lim                     : 2;
03037     uint32_t reserved_18_23               : 6;
03038     uint32_t err_bias                     : 8;
03039 #endif
03040     } s;

03164 /**

03168  * status. Typically the degraded threshold is less than the fail threshold.

03170 union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr {
03171     uint32_t u32;
03172     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr_s {
03173 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03174     uint32_t fail_th                      : 8;  /**< These bits provide the threshold value for
03175                                                          reporting an error condition due to a possibly
03176                                                          broken link.
03177                                                          0x00 = Disable the error rate failed threshold trigger.
03178                                                          0x01 = Set the error reporting threshold to 1.
03179                                                          0x02 = Set the error reporting threshold to 2.
03180                                                          - ...
03181                                                          0xFF = Set the error reporting threshold to 255. */
03182     uint32_t dgrad_th                     : 8;  /**< These bits provide the threshold value for
03183                                                          reporting an error condition due to a possibly
03184                                                          degrading link.
03185                                                          0x00 = Disable the degrade rate failed threshold trigger.
03186                                                          0x01 - Set the error reporting threshold to 1.
03187                                                          0x02 - Set the error reporting threshold to 2.
03188                                                          - ...
03189                                                          0xFF - Set the error reporting threshold to 255. */
03190     uint32_t reserved_0_15                : 16;
03191 #else
03192     uint32_t reserved_0_15                : 16;
03193     uint32_t dgrad_th                     : 8;
03194     uint32_t fail_th                      : 8;
03195 #endif
03196     } s;
03197     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr_s cn63xx;
03198     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr_s cn63xxp1;
03199     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr_s cn66xx;
03200     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_err_rate_thr_s cnf75xx;
03201 };

03406 /**
03407  * cvmx_sriomaint#_erb_lt_err_det
03408  *
03409  * This register indicates the error that was detected by the logical or transport logic layer.
03410  * Once a bit is set in this CSR, hardware will lock the register until software writes a zero to
03411  * clear all
03412  * the fields.  The hardware sets SRIO_INT_REG[LOG_ERB] every time it sets one of the bits.
03413  * To handle the interrupt, the following procedure may be best:
03414  *
03415  * (1) read this CSR, corresponding SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_ADDR_CAPT_H,
03416  * SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_ADDR_CAPT_L,
03417  * SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_DEV_ID_CAPT, and SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_CTRL_CAPT
03418  * (2) Write this CSR to 0.
03419  * (3) clear SRIO_INT_REG[LOG_ERB],
03420  */
03421 union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det {
03422     uint32_t u32;
03423     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_s {
03424 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03425     uint32_t io_err                       : 1;  /**< Received a response of ERROR for an IO logical
03426                                                          layer request.  This includes all maintenance and
03427                                                          memory responses not destined for the RX soft
03428                                                          packet FIFO. When SRIO receives an ERROR response
03429                                                          for a read, the issuing core or DPI DMA engine
03430                                                          receives result bytes with all bits set. In the
03431                                                          case of writes with response, this bit is the only
03432                                                          indication of failure. */
03433     uint32_t msg_err                      : 1;  /**< Received a response of ERROR for an outgoing
03434                                                          message segment. This bit is the only direct
03435                                                          indication of a MSG_ERR. When a MSG_ERR occurs,
03436                                                          SRIO drops the message segment and will not set
03437                                                          SRIO()_INT_REG[OMSG*] after the message
03438                                                          "transfer". NOTE: SRIO can continue to send or
03439                                                          retry other segments from the same message after
03440                                                          a MSG_ERR. */
03441     uint32_t gsm_err                      : 1;  /**< Received a response of ERROR for an GSM Logical
03442                                                          Request.  SRIO hardware never sets this bit. GSM
03443                                                          operations are not supported (outside of the Soft
03444                                                          Packet FIFO). */
03445     uint32_t msg_fmt                      : 1;  /**< Received an incoming message segment with a
03446                                                          formatting error.  A MSG_FMT error occurs when SRIO
03447                                                          receives a message segment with a reserved SSIZE,
03448                                                          or a illegal data payload size, or a MSGSEG greater
03449                                                          than MSGLEN, or a MSGSEG that is the duplicate of
03450                                                          one already received by an inflight message.
03451                                                          When a non-duplicate MSG_FMT error occurs, SRIO
03452                                                          drops the segment and sends an ERROR response.
03453                                                          When a duplicate MSG_FMT error occurs, SRIO
03454                                                          (internally) terminates the currently-inflight
03455                                                          message with an error and processes the duplicate,
03456                                                          which may result in a new message being generated
03457                                                          internally for the duplicate. */
03458     uint32_t ill_tran                     : 1;  /**< Received illegal fields in the request/response
03459                                                          packet for a supported transaction or any packet
03460                                                          with a reserved transaction type. When an ILL_TRAN
03461                                                          error occurs, SRIO ignores the packet. ILL_TRAN
03462                                                          errors are 2nd priority after ILL_TGT and may mask
03463                                                          other problems. Packets with ILL_TRAN errors cannot
03464                                                          enter the RX Soft Packet FIFO.
03465                                                          There are two things that can set ILL_TRAN:
03466                                                          (1) SRIO received a packet with a tt value is not
03467                                                          0 or 1, or (2) SRIO received a response to an
03468                                                          outstanding message segment whose status was not
03469                                                          DONE, RETRY, or ERROR. */
03470     uint32_t ill_tgt                      : 1;  /**< Received a packet that contained a destination ID
03471                                                          other than SRIOMAINT()_PRI_DEV_ID or
03472                                                          SRIOMAINT()_SEC_DEV_ID. When an ILL_TGT error
03473                                                          occurs, SRIO drops the packet. ILL_TGT errors are
03474                                                          highest priority, so may mask other problems.
03475                                                          Packets with ILL_TGT errors cannot enter the RX
03476                                                          soft packet fifo. */
03477     uint32_t msg_tout                     : 1;  /**< An expected incoming message request has not been
03478                                                          received within the time-out interval specified in
03479                                                          SRIOMAINT()_PORT_RT_CTL. When a MSG_TOUT occurs,
03480                                                          SRIO (internally) terminates the inflight message
03481                                                          with an error. */
03482     uint32_t pkt_tout                     : 1;  /**< A required response has not been received to an
03483                                                          outgoing memory, maintenance or message request
03484                                                          before the time-out interval specified in
03485                                                          SRIOMAINT()_PORT_RT_CTL.  When an IO or maintenance
03486                                                          read request operation has a PKT_TOUT, the issuing
03487                                                          core load or DPI DMA engine receive all ones for
03488                                                          the result. When an IO NWRITE_R has a PKT_TOUT,
03489                                                          this bit is the only indication of failure. When a
03490                                                          message request operation has a PKT_TOUT, SRIO
03491                                                          discards the the outgoing message segment,  and
03492                                                          this bit is the only direct indication of failure.
03493                                                          NOTE: SRIO may continue to send or retry other
03494                                                          segments from the same message. When one or more of
03495                                                          the segments in an outgoing message have a
03496                                                          PKT_TOUT, SRIO will not set SRIO()_INT_REG[OMSG*]
03497                                                          after the message "transfer". */
03498     uint32_t uns_resp                     : 1;  /**< An unsolicited/unexpected memory, maintenance or
03499                                                          message response packet was received that was not
03500                                                          destined for the RX soft packet FIFO.  When this
03501                                                          condition is detected, the packet is dropped. */
03502     uint32_t uns_tran                     : 1;  /**< A transaction is received that is not supported.
03503                                                          SRIO hardware will never set this bit - SRIO routes all
03504                                                          unsupported transactions to the RX soft packet
03505                                                          FIFO. */
03506     uint32_t reserved_1_21                : 21;
03507     uint32_t resp_sz                      : 1;  /**< Received an incoming memory or maintenance
03508                                                          read response packet with a DONE status and less
03509                                                          data then expected.  This condition causes the
03510                                                          Read to be completed and an error response to be
03511                                                          returned with all the data bits set to the issuing
03512                                                          core or DMA engine. */
03513 #else
03514     uint32_t resp_sz                      : 1;
03515     uint32_t reserved_1_21                : 21;
03516     uint32_t uns_tran                     : 1;
03517     uint32_t uns_resp                     : 1;
03518     uint32_t pkt_tout                     : 1;
03519     uint32_t msg_tout                     : 1;
03520     uint32_t ill_tgt                      : 1;
03521     uint32_t ill_tran                     : 1;
03522     uint32_t msg_fmt                      : 1;
03523     uint32_t gsm_err                      : 1;
03524     uint32_t msg_err                      : 1;
03525     uint32_t io_err                       : 1;
03526 #endif
03527     } s;
03528     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_s cn63xx;
03529     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_s cn63xxp1;
03530     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_s cn66xx;
03531     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_s cnf75xx;
03532 };
03533 typedef union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_det_t;

03535 /**
03536  * cvmx_sriomaint#_erb_lt_err_en
03537  *
03538  * This register contains the bits that control if an error condition locks the
03539  * logical/transport layer error detect and capture registers and is reported to the
03540  * system host.
03541  */
03542 union cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en {
03543     uint32_t u32;
03544     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en_s {
03545 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03546     uint32_t io_err                       : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an IO error response. Save and lock original request
03547                                                          transaction information in all logical/transport layer capture CSRs. */
03548     uint32_t msg_err                      : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of a message error response. Save and lock original request
03549                                                          transaction information in all logical/transport layer capture CSRs. */
03550     uint32_t gsm_err                      : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of a GSM error response. Save and lock original request
03551                                                          transaction capture information in all logical/transport layer capture CSRs. */
03552     uint32_t msg_fmt                      : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of a message format error. Save and lock transaction capture
03553                                                          information in logical/transport layer device ID and control capture CSRs. */
03554     uint32_t ill_tran                     : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an illegal transaction decode error Save and lock
03555                                                          transaction capture information in logical/transport layer device ID and control
03556                                                          capture CSRs. */
03557     uint32_t ill_tgt                      : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an illegal transaction target error. Save and lock
03558                                                          transaction capture information in logical/transport layer device ID and control
03559                                                          capture CSRs. */
03560     uint32_t msg_tout                     : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of a message request time-out error. Save and lock transaction
03561                                                          capture information in logical/transport layer device ID and control capture
03562                                                          CSRs for the last message request segment packet received. */
03563     uint32_t pkt_tout                     : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of a packet response time-out error. Save and lock original
03564                                                          request address in logical/transport layer address capture CSRs. Save and lock
03565                                                          original request destination ID in logical/transport layer device ID capture
03566                                                          CSR. */
03567     uint32_t uns_resp                     : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an unsolicited response error. Save and lock transaction
03568                                                          capture information in logical/transport layer device ID and control capture
03569                                                          CSRs. */
03570     uint32_t uns_tran                     : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an unsupported transaction error. Save and lock transaction
03571                                                          capture information in logical/transport layer device ID and control capture
03572                                                          CSRs. */
03573     uint32_t reserved_1_21                : 21;
03574     uint32_t resp_sz                      : 1;  /**< Enable reporting of an incoming response with unexpected data size. */
03575 #else
03576     uint32_t resp_sz                      : 1;
03577     uint32_t reserved_1_21                : 21;
03578     uint32_t uns_tran                     : 1;
03579     uint32_t uns_resp                     : 1;
03580     uint32_t pkt_tout                     : 1;
03581     uint32_t msg_tout                     : 1;
03582     uint32_t ill_tgt                      : 1;
03583     uint32_t ill_tran                     : 1;
03584     uint32_t msg_fmt                      : 1;
03585     uint32_t gsm_err                      : 1;
03586     uint32_t msg_err                      : 1;
03587     uint32_t io_err                       : 1;
03588 #endif
03589     } s;
03590     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en_s cn63xx;
03591     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en_s cn63xxp1;
03592     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en_s cn66xx;
03593     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_erb_lt_err_en_s cnf75xx;

03597 /**
03598  * cvmx_sriomaint#_erb_pack_capt_1
03599  *
03600  * This register contains either long symbol capture information or bytes 4
03601  * through 7 of the packet header. The hardware will not update this register (i.e. this

03603  * should only be read while this bit is set.

03669 /**

03671  *
03672  * This register contains either captured control symbol information or the first 4 bytes of
03673  * captured packet information.  The errors that generate partial control symbols can be found in
03674  * SRIOMAINT()_ERB_ERR_DET.  The hardware will not update this register (i.e. this register is
03675  * locked)

03684                                                          3 of packet header.

03687                                                          <23:21> = Stype 0.
03688                                                          <20:16> = Parameter 0.
03689                                                          <15:11> = Parameter 1.
03690                                                          <10:8> = Stype 1 (0 in partial symbol).
03691                                                          <7:5> = Command (0 in partial symbol).
03692                                                          <4:0> = CRC5    (0 in partial symbol). */

03704 /**
03705  * cvmx_sriomaint#_hb_dev_id_lock
03706  *
03707  * This register contains the device ID of the host responsible for initializing this SRIO
03708  * device. The register contains a special write once function that captures the first HOSTID
03709  * written to it after reset.  The function allows several potential hosts to write to this
03710  * register and then read it to see if they have responsibility for initialization.  The register
03711  * can be unlocked by rewriting the current host value.  This will reset the lock and restore the
03712  * value to 0xFFFF.
03713  */

03720 #else

03723 #endif
03724     } s;

03790 /**
03791  * cvmx_sriomaint#_ir_buffer_config2
03792  *
03793  * This register controls the RX and TX buffer availability by priority.  The typical values
03794  * are optimized for normal operation.  Care must be taken when changing these values to avoid
03795  * values which can result in deadlocks.  Disabling a priority is not recommended and can result
03796  * in system level failures.
03797  */
03798 union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2 {
03799     uint32_t u32;
03800     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2_s {
03801 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03802     uint32_t tx_wm3                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 3 packet
03803                                                          will be transmitted.  A value of 9 will disable
03804                                                          this priority. */
03805     uint32_t tx_wm2                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 2 packet
03806                                                          will be transmitted.  A value of 9 will disable
03807                                                          this priority. */
03808     uint32_t tx_wm1                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 1 packet
03809                                                          will be transmitted.  A value of 9 will disable
03810                                                          this priority. */
03811     uint32_t tx_wm0                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 0 packet
03812                                                          will be transmitted.  A value of 9 will disable
03813                                                          this priority. */
03814     uint32_t rx_wm3                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 3 packet
03815                                                          will be accepted.  A value of 9 will disable this
03816                                                          priority and always cause a physical layer RETRY. */
03817     uint32_t rx_wm2                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 2 packet
03818                                                          will be accepted.  A value of 9 will disable this
03819                                                          priority and always cause a physical layer RETRY. */
03820     uint32_t rx_wm1                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 1 packet
03821                                                          will be accepted.  A value of 9 will disable this
03822                                                          priority and always cause a physical layer RETRY. */
03823     uint32_t rx_wm0                       : 4;  /**< Number of buffers free before a priority 0 packet
03824                                                          will be accepted.  A value of 9 will disable this
03825                                                          priority and always cause a physical layer RETRY. */
03826 #else
03827     uint32_t rx_wm0                       : 4;
03828     uint32_t rx_wm1                       : 4;
03829     uint32_t rx_wm2                       : 4;
03830     uint32_t rx_wm3                       : 4;
03831     uint32_t tx_wm0                       : 4;
03832     uint32_t tx_wm1                       : 4;
03833     uint32_t tx_wm2                       : 4;
03834     uint32_t tx_wm3                       : 4;
03835 #endif
03836     } s;
03837     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2_s cn63xx;
03838     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2_s cn66xx;
03839     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2_s cnf75xx;
03840 };
03841 typedef union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2 cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_buffer_config2_t;

04025 /**
04026  * cvmx_sriomaint#_ir_sp_rx_ctrl
04027  *
04028  * This register is used to configure events generated by the reception of packets using the
04029  * soft packet FIFO.
04030  */
04031 union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl {
04032     uint32_t u32;
04033     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl_s {
04034 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04035     uint32_t reserved_1_31                : 31;
04036     uint32_t overwrt                      : 1;  /**< When clear, SRIO drops received packets that should
04037                                                          enter the soft packet FIFO when the FIFO is full.
04038                                                          In this case, SRIO also increments
04039                                                          SRIOMAINT()_IR_SP_RX_STAT[DROP_CNT]. When set, SRIO
04040                                                          stalls received packets that should enter the soft
04041                                                          packet FIFO when the FIFO is full. SRIO may stop
04042                                                          receiving any packets in this stall case if
04043                                                          software does not drain the receive soft packet
04044                                                          FIFO. */
04045 #else
04046     uint32_t overwrt                      : 1;
04047     uint32_t reserved_1_31                : 31;
04048 #endif
04049     } s;
04050     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl_s cn63xx;
04051     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl_s cn63xxp1;
04052     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl_s cn66xx;
04053     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_ctrl_s cnf75xx;

04057 /**
04058  * cvmx_sriomaint#_ir_sp_rx_data
04059  *
04060  * This register is used to read data from the soft packet FIFO.  The soft packet FIFO contains
04061  * the majority of the packet data received from the SRIO link.  The packet does not include the
04062  * control symbols or the initial byte containing AckId, 2 reserved bits and the CRF.  In the
04063  * case of packets with less than 80 bytes (including AckId byte) both the trailing CRC and pad
04064  * (if present) are included in the FIFO and octet count.  In the case of a packet with exactly
04065  * 80 bytes (including the AckId byte) the CRC is removed and the pad is maintained so the octet
04066  * count will read 81 bytes instead of the expected 83.  In cases over 80 bytes the CRC at 80
04067  * bytes
04068  * is removed but the trailing CRC and Pad (if necessary) are present.
04069  */
04070 union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data {
04071     uint32_t u32;
04072     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_s {
04073 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04074     uint32_t pkt_data                     : 32; /**< This register is used to read packet data from the RX FIFO. */
04075 #else
04076     uint32_t pkt_data                     : 32;
04077 #endif
04078     } s;
04079     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_s cn63xx;
04080     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_s cn63xxp1;
04081     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_s cn66xx;
04082     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_s cnf75xx;
04083 };
04084 typedef union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_data_t;
04085 
04086 /**
04087  * cvmx_sriomaint#_ir_sp_rx_stat
04088  *
04089  * This register is used to monitor the reception of packets using the soft packet FIFO.
04090  * The hardware sets SRIO_INT_REG[SOFT_RX] every time a packet arrives in the soft packet FIFO.
04091  * To read
04092  * out (one or more) packets, the following procedure may be best:
04093  *
04094  * (1) clear SRIO_INT_REG[SOFT_RX],
04095  *
04096  * (2) read this CSR to determine how many packets there are,
04097  *
04098  * (3) read the packets out (via SRIOMAINT()_IR_SP_RX_DATA).
04099  *
04100  * This procedure could lead to situations where SOFT_RX will be set even though there are
04101  * currently no packets the software interrupt handler would need to properly handle this case
04102  */
04103 union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat {
04104     uint32_t u32;
04105     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_s {
04106 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04107     uint32_t octets                       : 16; /**< This field shows how many octets are remaining
04108                                                          in the current packet in the RX FIFO. */
04109     uint32_t buffers                      : 4;  /**< This field indicates how many complete packets are
04110                                                          stored in the Rx FIFO. */
04111     uint32_t drop_cnt                     : 7;  /**< Number of Packets Received when the RX FIFO was
04112                                                          full and then discarded. */
04113     uint32_t full                         : 1;  /**< This bit is set when the value of Buffers Filled
04114                                                          equals the number of available reception buffers. */
04115     uint32_t fifo_st                      : 4;  /**< These bits display the state of the state machine
04116                                                          that controls loading of packet data into the RX
04117                                                          FIFO. The enumeration of states are as follows:
04118                                                          0x0 = Idle.
04119                                                          0x1 = Armed.
04120                                                          0x2 = Active.
04121                                                          _ All other states are reserved. */
04122 #else
04123     uint32_t fifo_st                      : 4;
04124     uint32_t full                         : 1;
04125     uint32_t drop_cnt                     : 7;
04126     uint32_t buffers                      : 4;
04127     uint32_t octets                       : 16;
04128 #endif
04129     } s;
04130     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_s cn63xx;
04131     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_cn63xxp1 {
04132 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04133     uint32_t octets                       : 16; /**< This field shows how many octets are remaining
04134                                                          in the current packet in the RX FIFO. */
04135     uint32_t buffers                      : 4;  /**< This field indicates how many complete packets are
04136                                                          stored in the Rx FIFO. */
04137     uint32_t reserved_5_11                : 7;
04138     uint32_t full                         : 1;  /**< This bit is set when the value of Buffers Filled
04139                                                          equals the number of available reception buffers.
04140                                                          This bit always reads zero in Pass 1 */
04141     uint32_t fifo_st                      : 4;  /**< These bits display the state of the state machine
04142                                                          that controls loading of packet data into the RX
04143                                                          FIFO. The enumeration of states are as follows:
04144                                                            0000 - Idle
04145                                                            0001 - Armed
04146                                                            0010 - Active
04147                                                            All other states are reserved. */
04148 #else
04149     uint32_t fifo_st                      : 4;
04150     uint32_t full                         : 1;
04151     uint32_t reserved_5_11                : 7;
04152     uint32_t buffers                      : 4;
04153     uint32_t octets                       : 16;
04154 #endif
04155     } cn63xxp1;
04156     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_s cn66xx;
04157     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_s cnf75xx;
04158 };
04159 typedef union cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat cvmx_sriomaintx_ir_sp_rx_stat_t;

04190 /**
04191  * cvmx_sriomaint#_ir_sp_tx_data
04192  *
04193  * This register is used to write data to the soft packet FIFO.  The format of the packet
04194  * follows the internal packet format (add link here).  Care must be taken on creating TIDs
04195  * for the packets which generate a response.  Bits [7:6] of the 8 bit TID must be set for
04196  * all Soft Packet FIFO generated packets.  TID values of 0x00 0xBF are reserved for hardware
04197  * generated Tags.  The remainer of the TID[5:0] must be unique for each packet in flight and
04198  * cannot be reused until a response is received in the SRIOMAINT()_IR_SP_RX_DATA register.
04199  */

04205                                                          TX FIFO. Reads of this register will return zero. */

04208 #endif
04209     } s;

04331 /**
04332  * cvmx_sriomaint#_lcs_ba0
04333  *
04334  * MSBs of SRIO address space mapped to maintenance BAR.
04335  * The double word aligned SRIO address window mapped to the SRIO maintenance BAR.  This window
04336  * has the highest priority and eclipses matches to the BAR0, BAR1 and BAR2 windows.
04337  * Note:  Address bits not supplied in the transfer are considered zero.  For example, SRIO
04338  * address 65:35 must be set to zero to match in a 34-bit access.  SRIO address 65:50 must be
04339  * set to zero to match in a 50-bit access.  This coding allows the maintenance bar window to
04340  * appear in specific address spaces. The remaining bits are located in SRIOMAINT()_LCS_BA1.
04341  * This SRIO maintenance BAR is effectively disabled when LCSBA[30] is set with 34 or 50-bit
04342  * addressing.
04343  */
04344 union cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0 {
04345     uint32_t u32;
04346     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0_s {
04347 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04348     uint32_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
04349     uint32_t lcsba                        : 31; /**< SRIO address 65:35. */
04350 #else
04351     uint32_t lcsba                        : 31;
04352     uint32_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
04353 #endif
04354     } s;
04355     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0_s      cn63xx;
04356     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0_s      cn63xxp1;
04357     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0_s      cn66xx;
04358     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_lcs_ba0_s      cnf75xx;
04359 };

04367  * has the highest priority and eclipses matches to the BAR0, BAR1 and BAR2 windows. Address
04368  * bits not supplied in the transfer are considered zero.  For example, SRIO address 65:35 must
04369  * be set to zero to match in a 34-bit access and SRIO address 65:50 must be set to zero to match
04370  * in a 50-bit access. This coding allows the maintenance bar window to appear in specific
04371  * address
04372  * spaces. Accesses through this BAR are limited to single word (32-bit) aligned transfers of one

04428 /**

04432  * This register specifies the SRIO address mapped to the BAR0 RSL space.  If the transaction
04433  * has not already been mapped to SRIO maintenance space through the SRIOMAINT_LCS_BA[1:0]

04435  * will map to OCTEON SLI registers.  34-bit address transactions require a match in SRIO
04436  * address 33:24 and require all the other bits in ADDR48, ADDR64 and ADDR66 fields to be zero.

04438  * ADDR64 and ADDR66 to be zero.  66-bit address transactions require matches of all valid
04439  * address
04440  * field bits.  Reads and writes through Bar0 have a size limit of 8 bytes and cannot cross
04441  * a 64-bit boundary.  All accesses with sizes greater than this limit will be ignored and return
04442  * an error on any SRIO responses.  Note: ADDR48 and ADDR64 fields are located in
04443  * SRIOMAINT()_M2S_BAR0_START0.  The ADDR32/66 fields of this register
04444  * are writeable over SRIO if the SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_ADR0] bit is zero.  The ENABLE field is
04445  * writeable over SRIO if the SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_BAR0] bit is zero.

04454 #else

04458 #endif

04521 /**
04522  * cvmx_sriomaint#_m2s_bar1_start1
04523  *
04524  * The starting SRIO address to forwarded to the BAR1 memory space.
04525  * This register specifies the SRIO address mapped to the BAR1 space.  If the
04526  * transaction has not already been mapped to SRIO maintenance space through the
04527  * SRIOMAINT_LCS_BA[1:0] registers and the address bits do not match enabled BAR0
04528  * addresses and if ENABLE is set and the addresses match the BAR1 addresses then
04529  * SRIO memory transactions will map to OCTEON memory space specified by
04530  * SRIOMAINT()_BAR1_IDX[31:0] registers.  The BARSIZE field determines the size of
04531  * BAR1, the entry select bits, and the size of each entry.
04532  *
04533  * * A 34-bit address matches BAR1 when it matches SRIO_Address[33:20+BARSIZE] while
04534  * all the other bits in ADDR48, ADDR64 and ADDR66 are zero.
04535  *
04536  * * A 50-bit address matches BAR1 when it matches SRIO_Address[49:20+BARSIZE] while
04537  * all the other bits of ADDR64 and ADDR66 are zero.
04538  *
04539  * * A 66-bit address matches BAR1 when all of SRIO_Address[65:20+BARSIZE] match all
04540  * corresponding address CSR field bits.
04541  *
04542  * Note: ADDR48 and
04543  * ADDR64 fields are located in SRIOMAINT()_M2S_BAR1_START0. The ADDR32/66 fields of
04544  * this register are writeable over SRIO if SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_ADR1] is zero.
04545  * The remaining fields are writeable over SRIO if SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_BAR1] is zero.
04546  */
04547 union cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1 {
04548     uint32_t u32;
04549     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1_s {
04550 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04551     uint32_t addr32                       : 12; /**< SRIO address 31:20.
04552                                                          This field is not used by the SRIO hardware for
04553                                                          BARSIZE values 12 or 13.
04554                                                          With BARSIZE < 12, the upper 12-BARSIZE
04555                                                          bits of this field are used, and the lower BARSIZE
04556                                                          bits of this field are unused by the SRIO hardware. */
04557     uint32_t reserved_7_19                : 13;
04558     uint32_t barsize                      : 4;  /**< Bar size.
04559                                                          <pre>
04560                                                                            SRIO_Address*
04561                                                                             ---------------------
04562                                                                            /                     \
04563                                                          BARSIZE         BAR     Entry   Entry    Entry
04564                                                          Value   BAR    compare  Select  Offset   Size
04565                                                          Size    bits    bits    bits
04566                                                          0       1MB    65:20   19:16   15:0     64KB
04567                                                          1       2MB    65:21   20:17   16:0    128KB
04568                                                          2       4MB    65:22   21:18   17:0    256KB
04569                                                          3       8MB    65:23   22:19   18:0    512KB
04570                                                          4      16MB    65:24   23:20   19:0      1MB
04571                                                          5      32MB    65:25   24:21   20:0      2MB
04572                                                          6      64MB    65:26   25:22   21:0      4MB
04573                                                          7     128MB    65:27   26:23   22:0      8MB
04574                                                          8     256MB    65:28   27:24   23:0     16MB
04575                                                          9     512MB    65:29   28:25   24:0     32MB
04576                                                          10    1024MB   65:30   29:26   25:0     64MB
04577                                                          11    2048MB   65:31   30:27   26:0    128MB
04578                                                          12    4096MB   65:32   31:28   27:0    256MB
04579                                                          13    8192MB   65:33   32:29   28:0    512MB
04580                                                          </pre> */
04581     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;  /**< SRIO address 65:64. */
04582     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< Enable BAR1 access. */
04583 #else
04584     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
04585     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;
04586     uint32_t barsize                      : 4;
04587     uint32_t reserved_7_19                : 13;
04588     uint32_t addr32                       : 12;
04589 #endif
04590     } s;
04591     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1_s cn63xx;
04592     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1_cn63xxp1 {
04593 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04594     uint32_t addr32                       : 12; /**< SRIO Address 31:20
04595                                                          With BARSIZE < 12, the upper 12-BARSIZE
04596                                                          bits of this field are used, and the lower BARSIZE
04597                                                          bits of this field are unused by the SRIO hardware. */
04598     uint32_t reserved_6_19                : 14;
04599     uint32_t barsize                      : 3;  /**< Bar Size.
04600                                                                               SRIO_Address*
04601                                                                          ---------------------
04602                                                                         /                     \
04603                                                          BARSIZE         BAR     Entry   Entry    Entry
04604                                                          Value   BAR    compare  Select  Offset   Size
04605                                                                  Size    bits    bits    bits
04606                                                           0       1MB    65:20   19:16   15:0     64KB
04607                                                           1       2MB    65:21   20:17   16:0    128KB
04608                                                           2       4MB    65:22   21:18   17:0    256KB
04609                                                           3       8MB    65:23   22:19   18:0    512KB
04610                                                           4      16MB    65:24   23:20   19:0      1MB
04611                                                           5      32MB    65:25   24:21   20:0      2MB
04612                                                           6      64MB    65:26   25:22   21:0      4MB
04613                                                           7     128MB    65:27   26:23   22:0      8MB
04614                                                           8     256MB  ** not in pass 1
04615                                                           9     512MB  ** not in pass 1
04616                                                          10       1GB  ** not in pass 1
04617                                                          11       2GB  ** not in pass 1
04618                                                          12       4GB  ** not in pass 1
04619                                                          13       8GB  ** not in pass 1
04620 
04621                                                          *The SRIO Transaction Address
04622                                                          The entry select bits is the X that  select an
04623                                                          SRIOMAINT(0..1)_BAR1_IDXX entry.
04624 
04625                                                          In O63 pass 2, BARSIZE is 4 bits (6:3 in this
04626                                                          CSR), and BARSIZE values 8-13 are implemented,
04627                                                          providing a total possible BAR1 size range from
04628                                                          1MB up to 8GB. */
04629     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;  /**< SRIO Address 65:64 */
04630     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< Enable BAR1 Access */
04631 #else
04632     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
04633     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;
04634     uint32_t barsize                      : 3;
04635     uint32_t reserved_6_19                : 14;
04636     uint32_t addr32                       : 12;
04637 #endif
04638     } cn63xxp1;
04639     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1_s cn66xx;
04640     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar1_start1_s cnf75xx;
04641 };

04644 /**
04645  * cvmx_sriomaint#_m2s_bar2_start
04646  *
04647  * The starting SRIO address to forwarded to the BAR2 memory space.
04648  * This register specifies the SRIO address mapped to the BAR2 space.  If ENABLE is set
04649  * and the address bits do not match the other enabled BAR address and match the BAR2
04650  * addresses then the SRIO memory transactions will map to OCTEON BAR2 memory space.
04651  * 34-bit address transactions require ADDR66, ADDR64 and ADDR48 fields set to zero
04652  * and supply zeros for unused local addresses 41:34.  50-bit address transactions a
04653  * match of SRIO address 49:42 and require all the other bits of ADDR64 and ADDR66 to
04654  * be zero. 66-bit address transactions require matches of all valid address field
04655  * bits. The ADDR32/48/64/66 fields of this register are writeable over SRIO if
04656  * SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_ADR2] is zero.  The remaining fields are writeable over SRIO
04657  * if SRIO()_ACC_CTRL[DENY_BAR2] is zero.
04658  */
04659 union cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start {
04660     uint32_t u32;
04661     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start_s {
04662 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04663     uint32_t addr64                       : 16; /**< SRIO address 63:48. */
04664     uint32_t reserved_6_15                : 10;
04665     uint32_t esx                          : 2;  /**< Endian swap mode used for SRIO 34-bit access.
04666                                                          For 50/66-bit assesses endian swap is determine
04667                                                          by ESX XOR'd with SRIO address 43:42.
04668                                                          0x0 = No swap.
04669                                                          0x1 = 64-bit swap bytes [ABCD_EFGH] -> [HGFE_DCBA].
04670                                                          0x2 = 32-bit swap words [ABCD_EFGH] -> [DCBA_HGFE].
04671                                                          0x3 = 32-bit word exch  [ABCD_EFGH] -> [EFGH_ABCD]. */
04672     uint32_t cax                          : 1;  /**< Cacheable access mode.  When set transfer is
04673                                                          cached.  This bit is used for SRIO 34-bit access.
04674                                                          For 50/66-bit accesses NCA is determine by CAX
04675                                                          XOR'd with SRIO address 44. */
04676     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;  /**< SRIO address 65:64. */
04677     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< Enable BAR2 access. */
04678 #else
04679     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
04680     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;
04681     uint32_t cax                          : 1;
04682     uint32_t esx                          : 2;
04683     uint32_t reserved_6_15                : 10;
04684     uint32_t addr64                       : 16;
04685 #endif
04686     } s;
04687     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start_cn63xx {
04688 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04689     uint32_t addr64                       : 16; /**< SRIO Address 63:48 */
04690     uint32_t addr48                       : 7;  /**< SRIO Address 47:41 */
04691     uint32_t reserved_6_8                 : 3;
04692     uint32_t esx                          : 2;  /**< Endian Swap Mode used for SRIO 34-bit access.
04693                                                          For 50/66-bit assesses Endian Swap is determine
04694                                                          by ESX XOR'd with SRIO Addr 39:38.
04695                                                          0 = No Swap
04696                                                          1 = 64-bit Swap Bytes [ABCD_EFGH] -> [HGFE_DCBA]
04697                                                          2 = 32-bit Swap Words [ABCD_EFGH] -> [DCBA_HGFE]
04698                                                          3 = 32-bit Word Exch  [ABCD_EFGH] -> [EFGH_ABCD] */
04699     uint32_t cax                          : 1;  /**< Cacheable Access Mode.  When set transfer is
04700                                                          cached.  This bit is used for SRIO 34-bit access.
04701                                                          For 50/66-bit accessas NCA is determine by CAX
04702                                                          XOR'd with SRIO Addr 40. */
04703     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;  /**< SRIO Address 65:64 */
04704     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< Enable BAR2 Access */
04705 #else
04706     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
04707     uint32_t addr66                       : 2;
04708     uint32_t cax                          : 1;
04709     uint32_t esx                          : 2;
04710     uint32_t reserved_6_8                 : 3;
04711     uint32_t addr48                       : 7;

04713 #endif
04714     } cn63xx;
04715     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start_cn63xx cn63xxp1;
04716     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start_cn63xx cn66xx;
04717     struct cvmx_sriomaintx_m2s_bar2_start_cnf75xx {
04718 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04719     uint32_t addr64                       : 16; /**< SRIO address 63:48. */
04720     uint32_t addr48                       : 3;  /**< SRIO address 47:45. */
04721     uint32_t reserved_6_12                : 7;

04890 /**
